Samson Folarin The Lagos State House of Assembly has warned that any contractor that accesses mobilisation fees and absconds or does not carry out the job commensurate with the fee paid will be jailed for two years or a fine equivalent to the fee paid or both. A statement on Wednesday said this was disclosed during a public hearing organised by the House Committee on Procurement to amend the Lagos State Public Procurement Agency Law Cap. L56, Laws of Lagos State, 2015. The Speaker, Mudashiru Obasa, who was represented by the Deputy Speaker, Sanni Wasiu-Eshinlokun, in his keynote address, assured that all comments and observations by stakeholders would be looked into. According to the Majority Leader, Sanai Agunbiade, the Lagos State Public Procurement Agency (Amendment) Bill 2020, has 82 sections and only 38 sections will be amended. One of them is Section 22(4) (b) which provides that “Any supplier, contractor or service provider acting jointly under the provisions of the law shall be jointly and severely liable for all obligations, responsibilities and non-performance or improper performance of any contract arising from the provisions of this law.” The Chairman, House Committee on Procurement, Rauf Sulaiman, implored the stakeholders to contribute their observations in respect to all the amendments, while assuring that their inputs would be considered. Copyright PUNCH.
